'''Sashino Shrine''' is a [[Shinto shrines]]. As a [[Religious Corporation]] (宗教法人), there are four such shrines in Japan.
* {{ill|Sashino Shrine (Kasama)|ja|佐志能神社 (笠間市)|12=draft|12=draft}} (さしのうじんじゃ) - Located in [[Kasama]], [[Ibaraki Prefecture]]. Listed in the [[Engishiki Jinmyocho|Engishiki]] as a minor shrine (式内小社). Classified as a village shrine (村社) under the [[Modern system of ranked Shinto shrines|modern shrine ranking system]]. * {{ill|Sashino Shrine (Ishioka Kakio)|ja|佐志能神社 (石岡市柿岡)|12=draft|12=draft}} (さしのじんじゃ) - Located in [[Ishioka]], Kakio, Ibaraki Prefecture. Also listed in the Engishiki as a minor shrine. Classified as a village shrine (村社). * {{ill|Sashino Shrine (Ishioka Someya)|ja|佐志能神社 (石岡市染谷)|12=draft|12=draft}} (さしのじんじゃ) - Located in Someya and Murakami, Ishioka, Ibaraki Prefecture. Listed in the Engishiki as a minor shrine. Classified as a district shrine (郷社).
